#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:1
msgid "digiKam Main Window Search View"
msgstr "Pogled iskanja glavnega okna digiKam"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:1
msgid "digiKam, documentation, user manual, photo management, open source, free, learn, easy, advanced, search"
msgstr "digiKam, dokumentacija, uporabniški priročnik, upravljanje fotografij, odprta koda, brezplačno, učenje, enostavno, napredno, iskanje"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:14
msgid "Search View"
msgstr "Pogled iskanja"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:16
msgid "We talked about quite a few views already and their searching capabilities, which are all kind of specialized. The Search View now offers a more versatile and general way of searching. There are two different approaches."
msgstr "Govorili smo že o kar nekaj pogledih in njihovih zmožnostih iskanja, ki so vsi nekako specializirani. Iskalni pogled zdaj ponuja bolj vsestranski in splošni način iskanja. Obstajata dva različna pristopa."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:22
msgid "The digiKam Simple Search Tool"
msgstr "Preprosto iskalno orodje digiKam"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:24
msgid "In the field right below you can enter a title and save your selection. It will then appear in the **Searches** list field below. But the best is still to come: the Timeline View offers a search for a search! If you have a lot more searches saved than my ridiculous four in the screenshot the adaptive search field at the bottom may help to find a certain search."
msgstr "V polje desno spodaj lahko vnesete naslov in shranite izbiro. Nato se prikaže v spodnjem polju seznama **Iskanja**. Najboljše pa šele prihaja: pogled časovne premice ponuja iskanje za iskanjem! Če imate shranjenih veliko več iskanj kot mojih smešnih štirih na posnetku zaslona, vam lahko prilagodljivo iskalno polje na dnu pomaga najti določeno iskanje."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:27
msgid "The Quick Search"
msgstr "Hitro iskanje"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:29
msgid "Quick Search is the adaptive search box at the top of the search dialog (Left Sidebar) and provides you with a simple means to search the digiKam database with a single query. You can enter any arguments in the **Search** text field and it will be used to determine the results. For instance, you can enter the string \"birthday\" to search the complete database for occurrences of the word \"birthday\" in all metadata text fields, or \"05.webp\" to search for a specific image file name \"05.webp\" (no escaping as in reg-expressions needed)."
msgstr "Hitro iskanje je prilagodljivo iskalno polje na vrhu iskalnega pogovornega okna (leva stranska vrstica) in vam omogoča preprosto iskanje po bazi podatkov digiKam z eno samo poizvedbo. V besedilno polje **Išči** lahko vnesete poljubne argumente, ki bodo uporabljeni za določitev rezultatov. Vnesete lahko na primer niz »birthday«, če želite v celotni zbirki podatkov poiskati pojavitve besede »birthday« v vseh besedilnih poljih metapodatkov, ali »05.webp«, če želite poiskati določeno ime slikovne datoteke »05.webp« (ni potrebnega ubežnega znaka kot v regularnih izrazih)."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:31
msgid "Search Properties:"
msgstr "Lastnosti iskanja:"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:33
msgid "Searches are case insensitive."
msgstr "Iskanja ne razlikujejo med velikimi in malimi črkami."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:35
msgid "Blank separated search terms are boolean AND combinations."
msgstr "Prazno ločeni iskalni izrazi so logične IN kombinacije."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:37
msgid "Special characters are literal and not interpreted ( . * ? / etc.)."
msgstr "Posebni znaki so dobesedni in se ne interpretirajo ( . * ? / itd.)."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:39
msgid "Include all elements of the database: names, rating, keywords, tags, albums, collections, dates (and more in the future)."
msgstr "Vključite vse elemente baze podatkov: imena, ocene, ključne besede, oznake, albume, zbirke, datume (in še več v prihodnosti)."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:41
msgid "You can save your searches as a live folder that always filters for what you entered as search criteria. Just type a name for the search into the **Save Current Search** field and click the **Save** button to the right of it. When saved, the filter will appear in the **Searches** list. By clicking the title bar of this list you can invert the sorting order. Once you select one of your saved searches, the search result will be presented in the Image Area immediately and the **Save Current Search** field will convert into a **Edit Stored Search** field where you can edit your search criteria. The name of the saved search will be used to label the search result in the Image Area."
msgstr "Svoja iskanja lahko shranite kot živo mapo, ki vedno filtrira tisto, kar ste vnesli kot merila iskanja. Preprosto vnesite ime za iskanje v polje **Shrani trenutno iskanje** in kliknite gumb **Shrani** na desni strani. Ko je filter shranjen, se bo pojavil na seznamu **Iskanja**. S klikom na naslovno vrstico tega seznama lahko obrnete vrstni red razvrščanja. Ko izberete eno od svojih shranjenih iskanj, bo rezultat iskanja takoj prikazan v območju slik in polje **Shrani trenutno iskanje** se bo spremenilo v polje **Urejanje shranjenega iskanja**, kjer lahko uredite iskalne kriterije. Ime shranjenega iskanja bo uporabljeno za označevanje rezultatov iskanja v območju slike."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:43
msgid "If you want to delete or rename a saved search from the list, click with the right mouse button on it and select from the context menu."
msgstr "Če želite izbrisati ali preimenovati shranjeno iskanje s seznama, kliknite z desno miškino tipko nanj in izberite v kontekstnem meniju."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:48
msgid "The Advanced Search Tool"
msgstr "Orodje za napredno iskanje"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:50
msgid "Advanced Search tool provides an extended search form which can be used to search in specific fields of the digiKam database in a more sophisticated way. Click the **New Advanced Search...** button and it will come up like this:"
msgstr "Orodje za napredno iskanje nudi razširjen obrazec za iskanje, ki ga je mogoče uporabiti za iskanje v določenih poljih baze podatkov digiKam na bolj sofisticiran način. Kliknite gumb **Novo napredno iskanje...** in prikazalo se bo takole:"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:56
msgid "The digiKam Advanced Search Tool"
msgstr "Orodje za napredno iskanje digiKam"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:58
msgid "The field labeled **Find items that have associated all these words:** is just a duplicate of the Quick Search field."
msgstr "Polje z oznako **Najdi elemente, ki so povezani z vsemi temi besedami:** je le dvojnik polja za hitro iskanje."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:60
msgid "Click on one of the blue categories and there will fold out an area with all the fields you can search for in that very category. Depending on the kind of data each field contains different input fields for your search, sometimes more than one type for the same field. Simplest are selection buttons, e.g. for colors. Then you have plain fields of the “The field content contains type\", drop down lists and checkboxes. Many fields have two input fields allowing you to define a range, e.g. **Find items with a width between**. And often you find a link type thing called \"Any\" which opens a drop down field with checkboxes for the possible contents of that field."
msgstr "Kliknite eno od modrih kategorij in odprlo se bo območje z vsemi polji, ki jih lahko iščete v tej kategoriji. Glede na vrsto podatkov vsako polje vsebuje različna vnosna polja za vaše iskanje, včasih več kot eno vrsto za isto polje. Najenostavnejši so izbirni gumbi, npr. za barve. Nato imate navadna polja spustnih seznamov in potrditvenih polj »Vsebina polja vsebuje vrsto«. Veliko polj ima dve vnosni polji, ki vam omogočata, da določite obseg, npr. **Poišči elemente s širino med**. In pogosto najdete stvar tipa povezave, imenovana \"Kateri koli\", ki odpre spustno polje s potrditvenimi polji za možno vsebino tega polja."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:66
msgid "The digiKam Advanced Search Criteria"
msgstr "Kriteriji naprednega iskanja digiKam"

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:68
msgid "Thanks to the labeling of the search fields they are pretty much self explaining. What we have to talk about is how they work together if you fill in or select more than one. On the right side of the header (blue area at the top) you find a little link **Options**. If you click on that one the header will change and you see four options."
msgstr "Zahvaljujoč označevanju iskalnih polj so precej samoumevna. Pogovoriti se moramo o tem, kako delujejo skupaj, če izpolnite ali izberete več kot enega. Na desni strani glave (modro območje na vrhu) najdete majhno povezavo **Možnosti**. Če kliknete na to, se bo glava spremenila in videli boste štiri možnosti."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:70
msgid "**Meet All of the following conditions** means that your different search parameters will be connected by boolean AND for the search. Example: if you selected Album name “Holidays” and color “red” the search will find all pictures labeled with “red” out of the Album “Holidays”."
msgstr "**Izpolnjevanje vseh naslednjih pogojev** pomeni, da bodo vaši različni iskalni parametri povezani z logičnim IN za iskanje. Primer: če ste izbrali ime albuma \"Dopust\" in barvo \"rdeča\", bo iskanje našlo vse slike, označene z \"rdečo\", iz albuma \"Dopust\"."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:72
msgid "**Meet Any of the following conditions** means that your different search parameters will be connected by boolean OR for the search. Example: if you selected Album name “Holidays” and color “red” the search will find the content of the Album “Holidays” and all pictures labeled with “red” out of your whole collection."
msgstr "**Izpolnjevanje katerega koli od naslednjih pogojev** pomeni, da bodo vaši različni iskalni parametri povezani z logičnim ALI za iskanje. Primer: če ste izbrali ime albuma \"Prazniki\" in barvo \"rdeča\", bo iskanje našlo vsebino albuma \"Prazniki\" in vse slike, označene z \"rdeče\", iz vaše celotne zbirke."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:74
msgid "**None of these conditions are met** means that your different search parameters will be connected by boolean NAND for the search. Again our example: if you selected Album name “Holidays” and color “red” the search will find all pictures of your collection except those labeled with “red” and except those out of the Album “Holidays”."
msgstr "**Noben od teh pogojev ni izpolnjen** pomeni, da bodo vaši različni iskalni parametri povezani z logičnim \"ne in\" za iskanje. Ponovno naš primer: če ste izbrali ime albuma \"Prazniki\" in barvo \"rdeča\", bo iskanje našlo vse slike vaše zbirke razen tistih, ki so označene z \"rdeče\" in razen tistih iz albuma \"Prazniki\"."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:76
msgid "**At least one of these conditions is not met** means that your different search parameters will be connected by boolean NOR for the search. One more example: if you selected Album name “Holidays” and color “red” the search will find all pictures of your collection except those labeled with “red” out of the Album “Holidays”."
msgstr "**Vsaj eden od teh pogojev ni izpolnjen** pomeni, da bodo vaši različni iskalni parametri povezani z logičnim \"ne ali\" za iskanje. Še en primer: če ste izbrali ime albuma \"Prazniki\" in barvo \"rdeča\", bo iskanje našlo vse slike vaše zbirke razen tistih, ki so označene z \"rdeče\" iz albuma \"Prazniki\"."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:78
msgid "Complicated? No, good! Because the real stuff is yet to come. Have a look at the footer of the Advanced Search Tool. Here you find **+ Add Search Group**. If you hit this button another list with the same categories of search fields will open below the first one (scroll down in case you don't see it right away) separated by a blue header showing the same options we were just talking about. On top of them you see an underlined OR meaning that this list is connected to the first one by boolean OR. You can change that to AND by clicking on it."
msgstr "Zapleteno? Slabo! Ker tisto pravo šele pride. Oglejte si nogo orodja za napredno iskanje. Tukaj najdete **+ Dodaj iskalno skupino**. Če pritisnete ta gumb, se pod prvim odpre drug seznam z istimi kategorijami iskalnih polj (pomaknite se navzdol, če ga ne vidite takoj), ločen z modro glavo, ki prikazuje iste možnosti, o katerih smo ravnokar govorili. Na vrhu vidite podčrtan ALI, kar pomeni, da je ta seznam s prvim povezan z logičnim ALI. To lahko spremenite v IN s klikom nanj."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:80
msgid "To explain how it works let's make another example based on one of those we had already. I want to use the second one. That means: in the first group you checked **Meet Any of the following conditions** and you selected Album name “Holidays” and color “red”. As we said already this will produce all pictures labeled with “red” out of your whole collection and the content of the Album “Holidays”. Now let's assume for some reason you want to exclude all rejected files and all files with a rating lower than three stars."
msgstr "Da pojasnimo, kako deluje, naredimo še en primer, ki temelji na enem od tistih, ki smo jih že imeli. Želim uporabiti drugega. To pomeni: v prvi skupini ste označili **Izpolnjevati katerega koli od naslednjih pogojev** in izbrali ime albuma “Prazniki” in barvo “rdeča”. Kot smo že povedali, bodo s tem nastale vse slike, označene z \"rdečo\", iz vaše celotne zbirke in vsebine albuma \"Prazniki\". Zdaj pa predpostavimo, da želite iz nekega razloga izključiti vse zavrnjene datoteke in vse datoteke z oceno, nižjo od treh zvezdic."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:82
msgid "So you open a second group, click on the underlined OR in the header in order to change it to AND, select **None of these conditions are met**, fold out the **Picture Properties**, check under **Labels** the red flag (rejected) and select under **Rating** no star (five white stars) in the first field and two stars in the second field. Note that there is a difference between **No star** and **No Rating assigned**! If you want to exclude the pictures without any rating as well you got to open another Search Group, click on the underlined OR in the header in order to change it to AND, select **None of these conditions are met** and select **No Rating assigned** in the **Picture Properties** category."
msgstr "Torej odprete drugo skupino, kliknete na podčrtan ALI v glavi, da ga spremenite v IN, izberete **Noben od teh pogojev ni izpolnjen**, razgrnete **Lastnosti slike**, preverite pod **Oznake ** rdečo zastavico (zavrnjeno) in pod **Ocena** izberite brez zvezdice (pet belih zvezdic) v prvem polju in dve zvezdici v drugem polju. Upoštevajte, da obstaja razlika med **Brez zvezdice** in **Brez dodeljene ocene**! Če želite izključiti tudi slike brez kakršne koli ocene, morate odpreti drugo iskalno skupino, kliknite podčrtan ALI v glavi, da ga spremenite v IN, izberite **Noben od teh pogojev ni izpolnjen** in izberite * *Brez dodeljene ocene** v kategoriji **Lastnosti slike**."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:84
msgid "Which brings us to the fact that you can open as many additional Search Groups as you need to formulate your query. But since the purpose of this handbook is not to open a competition in creating the most sophisticated queries I leave it to you to figure out how far you have to go or can go in this respect and rather finish this section with a few hints about the other buttons in the Advanced Search Tool."
msgstr "Kar nas pripelje do dejstva, da lahko odprete toliko dodatnih iskalnih skupin, kot jih potrebujete za oblikovanje vaše poizvedbe. Ker pa namen tega priročnika ni odpreti tekmovanja v ustvarjanju najzahtevnejših poizvedb, prepuščam vam, da ugotovite, kako daleč morate iti ali lahko greste v tem pogledu, in ta razdelek raje zaključite z nekaj namigi o druge gumbe v orodju za napredno iskanje."

#: ../../main_window/search_view.rst:86
msgid "Beside the **+ Add Search Group** button you see Reset. This removes all additional Search Groups and clears all the fields in the remaining one. It's a good policy to use this button before starting to create a new search, in particular when you leave the Advanced Search Tool with the intention to use the Quick Search for your next query, because otherwise the search criteria remain active even if you don't see them and screw up your new search. Try carries out the search but leaves the Advanced Search Tool window open, OK does the same but closes the window. **Remove Group** in the header of the additional Search Groups doesn't need an explanation."
msgstr "Poleg gumba **+ Dodaj iskalno skupino** vidite Ponastavi. S tem odstranite vse dodatne iskalne skupine in počistite vsa polja v preostali skupini. Priporočljivo je, da uporabite ta gumb, preden začnete ustvarjati novo iskanje, zlasti ko zapustite napredno iskalno orodje z namenom, da uporabite hitro iskanje za svojo naslednjo poizvedbo, saj drugače iskalni kriteriji ostanejo aktivni, tudi če ne jih ne vidite in zajebete svoje novo iskanje. Poskusi izvede iskanje, vendar pusti okno orodja za napredno iskanje odprto, V redu naredi isto, vendar zapre okna. **Odstrani skupino** v glavi dodatnih iskalnih skupin ne potrebuje razlage."
